9) PS. My last day on the daily will be 11/10. I look forward to watching the show evolve into a new era. And will stay tuned!!
8) I didn’t realize I was stepping onto a rocket ship when I moved to San Francisco to launch B-Tech in 2010. Time to launch the next one! I hope you join me for the ride.🚀
7) Not gonna lie. I’m overwhelmed with emotions right now. When I saw the official announcement this morning, my daughter said “Something came out of mommy’s phone and she’s crying!” But it’s time…
6) I’m so grateful to my incredible team, my colleagues, my family and to Bloomberg for giving me the opportunity to take the story this far, and now, even farther. https://t.co/1HrU9KyfVl

5) Bloomberg Tech has been my inspiration, my family, my home -- thousands of interviews, 4 kids, writing Brotopia, a few cameos on HBO’s Silicon Valley, and so many unimaginable memories... https://t.co/KnGiNq9uGu

4) This will require stepping back from my daily show. I’ll still conduct big interviews & contribute to major stories at Bloomberg, and this new format will give me more freedom to delve deeper, spark new joy, and reach new audiences.

3) Tech has thrust us into the middle of a massive experiment in human history, and no one knows for sure where it will lead us next. I want to explore how society, life, WE are changing and take you with me...

2) I will be working with the amazing team at Bloomberg to develop new shows at the intersection of tech, business & culture. We’re starting by turning Studio 1.0 into a premium weekly interview program & will follow w/ innovative limited series. Think capture the zeitgeist!!
1) After 12 years sitting in the Bloomberg Technology anchor chair, I’m starting a new chapter -- and I’m so excited to finally share it with all of you…. https://t.co/MVRyr6z3eq

The future of CNN & the business case for CNN+ according to @morsea from our #SXSW22 chat, by @Lucas_Shaw 

https://t.co/qevdVGaC5Z

--Will there be less opinion, more straight news? "Every news organization in the US tends to do a bit of a rethink every political cycle. That's natural."
--"We never abandoned straight news storytelling... we never abandoned news."
--no formal talks yet w/ Discovery's David Zaslav, incoming CNN president Chris Licht about CNN's future due to the quiet period post-shareholder vote

--departure of Jeff Zucker was "sad and shocking" 
--"We've all been doing our best to lead thru a pretty difficult period." 
--Morse says he did not know about Zucker's relationship with Allison Gollust but that "the rules apply to everybody."

--deals with Apple, Roku, Comcast secured, still working on others
--cited NYT as model for a multi-faceted subscription business

From my chat w/ @morsea re: CNN+

--it's CNN's most ambitious undertaking since the network's launch
--budget is "orders of magnitude larger" than anything CNN has taken on, but he's confident it will be profitable "within a few years," grow substantial subscriber base quickly
